Hair requires lots of care throughout the summer to keep it looking soft and shiny. Here are a few tips to help you with your summer haircare regime. This blog will help you combat these and allow you to enjoy healthy hair in the sun. 
</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-7fc6" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jHkVzv kFoSDU pf-24_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-dVNjXY gaVfQc"><div class="sc-llYSUQ bhKSKZ pf-25_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-26_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-iUKqMP iPshnk pf-27_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-29_">Say goodbye to faded hair</span></h3></div></div></div><div class="sc-llYSUQ bhKSKZ pf-30_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-31_"><div title="Caring for Your Hair in The Summer: Hair Hacks for Hot Weather" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-jObWnj dWwBay pf-32_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/say-goodbye-to-faded-hair-1666016268719.jpg?v=1666016269" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/say-goodbye-to-faded-hair-1666016268719.jpg?v=1666016269 1536w" width="424" height="600" alt="how to care for your hair in summer at home" title="Caring for Your Hair in The Summer: Hair Hacks for Hot Weather"/></div><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-35_">The sun can be lovely for enhancing your natural highlights which we all have (some people’s are more obvious than others). The sun however is one of the biggest culprits for fading your dyed hair and your extensions. If you have red hair unfortunately you are more likely to lose your pazzaz in the sun. Although everyone’s hair reacts differently but the way to imagine it is that the sun causes something like cracks and your colour leaks out of them. <p> </p>

